#: audio_describer/core/audio_describer.py:37
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Analyze this video segment. Identify every distinct character who "
"appears. For each character, provide:\n"
"    1. A unique ID (e.g., \"man_in_red_shirt\", \"woman_with_glasses\"). Use "
"underscores.\n"
"    2. A definitive physical description (e.g., \"A tall man with glasses "
"and a grey suit.\").\n"
"    3. The character's name, if and only if it is spoken clearly in the "
"segment and can be unambiguously linked to them. If the name is not spoken "
"or the link is ambiguous, this field must be null.\n"
"    \n"
"    Return this as a single JSON object with a single key \"characters\" "
"which contains a list of these character objects.\n"
"    Example: {\"characters\": [{\"id\": \"man_in_suit\", \"description\": "
"\"A man in a dark suit.\", \"name\": \"David\"}]}\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

